Alice Clara HECK et al. v. J. M. ALEXANDER. J. M. ALEXANDER v. Alice Clara HECK et al. Nos. 3838, 3839. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Feb. 2, 1949. H. A-. Kiker and Charles C. Spann, both of Santa Fe., N. M., and John B. Wright, of Raton, N. M., for Alice Clara Heck et al. E. T. Brooks, of Abilene, Tex., for J. M. Alexander.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and SYMES, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal and cross-appeal dismissed, pursuant to stipulation.
